The Pulse™ PIVL (Pulsatile Intravascular Lithotripsy) System | AVS Pulse Skip to main content Image The Pulse™ PIVL (Pulsatile Intravascular Lithotripsy) System Pressure waves shatter intravascular calcium and expand the lesion to restore blood flow AVS Pulse Main navigation About Us AVS Overview Meet Our Team Technology Pulsatile Intravascular Lithotripsy Foundational Evidence News & Events Contact The Pulse™ PIVL (Pulsatile Intravascular Lithotripsy) System Take a closer look Pulsatile Intravascular Lithotripsy utilizes low intensity, high frequency pressure waves to generate fractures in the plaque and expand stenotic lesions to restore blood Waves are delivered to calcified vessels through a noncompliant balloon that simultaneously fragments calcium and dilates the artery during the same treatment Cross Cross the lesion with the PIVL Catheter delivered over an ” Prime to atm to enable energy Image Image Pulse , pulses are transmitted by the balloon to the calcium, initiating Shatter PIVL therapy cracks intimal and medial calcium, increasing vessel elasticity Image Image Expand The PIVL balloon enables the expansion of the surrounding soft tissues to maximize luminal gain Pulse System Components Three simple components for easy integration into your endovascular lab Pulse IVL Amplifier & Balloon Catheter High intensity, low attenuation pulse energy generation Low crossing profile Pulse IVL Console Intuitive User Interface Optimizes energy delivery based on lesion compliance Pulse IVL Handle Ergonomic handle for clinician interaction Image Keep Your Finger on Gennao Bio - , Targeted Nucleic Acid Therapeutics Skip to content Menu Menu About Technology Advantages Team News Careers Contact Menu About Technology Advantages Team News Careers Contact , Targeted Nucleic Acid Therapeutics Gennao Bio is developing , targeted nucleic acid therapeutics utilizing its proprietary, GMAB platform GMAB is an adaptive technology that uses a antibody to bind to and deliver therapeutic levels of a wide variety of nucleic acid payloads to select We are developing this delivery system with an initial focus in oncology and rare monogenic skeletal muscle Technology Our gene monoclonal antibody (GMAB) technology has several unique attributes that enable it to systemically deliver multiple types of nucleic acids, directly into the cell, while preserving therapeutic 1 Adaptive and flexible Our antibody binds to a broad range of nucleic acid payloads including double-stranded RNA, mRNA, synthetic RNA, DNA, RNAi and Additionally, GMAB complexes have demonstrated the ability to be delivered into both the cytoplasm and the 2 Targeted delivery GMAB complexes target the nucleoside transporter ENT2, which is highly expressed on tumors cells and skeletal Specificity for ENT2 allows for better targeting toward relevant cell types while minimizing 3 Preserves therapeutic function In preclinical studies, GMAB complexes have demonstrated the ability to protect a wide range of nucleic acid payloads including mRNA after systemic delivery thereby preserving structural integrity and biological function of the GMAB Technology Advantages Our GMAB technology has the potential to transform genetic medicine by offering meaningful advantages over viral & other nucleic acid delivery , Systemic Delivery binds to multiple types of nucleic acid payloads Delivery of molecules Targeted Cell Transduction Selective targeting of ENT2 Cell penetration into cytoplasm and nucleus Dosing Flexibility Repeat dosing with ability to escalate and titrate dose Dosing possible regardless of age, weight and medical condition Improved Safety Profile Devoid of immune response Clinical data suggest GMAB is safe and well tolerated Utilizes mAb Manufacturing Littlebird | Littlebird Connected Care ENDING SOON - FREE SHIPPING ON ALL ORDERS ENDING SOON - FREE FALL SHIPPING ON ALL ORDERS Shop Blog 0 Shop Blog Home Littlebird Littlebird  Filter by tag: Childcare Connected Care parenting Sleep Sunday Scaries Toddler Essentials Wellness working Working Mom I Am A Bad Sep , Posted by: Megan Colarossi I AM A BAD By: Monica Plath …Or at least that is what one social media commentator wrote on a recent news clip of my children and Truth be told, there are a lot of moments where I would agree with Parenting is hard and even harder when I am doing my I constantly feel like I should do That’s the “I bet she makes macaroni and cheese from a box,” said another online Well if that is the bar for BAD MOMS then at least I know I have some company! As parents, we are all fighting daily battles to get through the mental gymnastics of schedules, meals, enrichment, and family, and somehow make time to be ourselves while being The TV news segment in question took me from the sanctuary of privacy in to a public I simply wanted to tell my story about how motherhood spurred me to innovation as I saw a much needed change in It was not long into my first pregnancy that I realized the “village” that other generations spoke about in reference to raising children was THE VILLAGE IS DIGITAL shouted the mom bloggers and mommy sites, which was great for scrolling on sleepless BUT who was there to catch me when I fell? The support system that came together for my family was a mesh of babysitters who became like sisters, friends who picked up the phone when their own children were crying, and daycare providers who let me drop my children off an hour early so I could make an appointment before work, and the extended family that went out of their way to help me create my family’s version of Even in our woke era, the stigma of the “working mom” still burns more than the “working ” For those of us that don’t have a choice to not to work, it is a burden that follows us as society where “they” expect us to “work like we don’t have children, and parent like we don’t ” The struggle and balance is very real and Well, I guess I am a "BAD MOM" because I need to provide for my family and that upsets some people’s However, I am a "GREAT MOM" because I give myself grace and do my damn best every day while showing up for my family and To all the working moms, dads, care providers, and everyone in between - you are enough! Technology | JTEC Energy About Mission Core Values Team Technology Overview Deeper Dive Applications News Careers Contact About Mission Core Values Team Technology Overview Deeper Dive Applications News Careers Contact The JTEC harvests thermal energy to create electricity A schematic of the JTEC device is shown In the device, there is a hot side (right) and a cool side (left). Each side contains a Membrane Electrode Assembly (MEA) stack consisting of a membrane and porous electrodes on the top and The membranes separate regions that contain hydrogen (H 2 ) gas with different pressures, and they are permeable to protons (H + ) but are largely impermeable to H 2 The bottom region contains high pressure and the top region contains low During operation, H 2 gas on the hot (right) side of the device is oxidized in the region, and the resulting H + ions travel through the membrane and are reduced to H 2 at the pressure This is a spontaneous process driven by the pressure Simultaneously, the reaction is driven in reverse at the (left) side: the H 2 gas is oxidized in the region, and the resulting H + ions travel through the membrane and are reduced to H 2 at the This process is not spontaneous, but some of the voltage produced on the hot side is used to drive this process at the cold The reason this device is able to operate is because the voltage (Voc) produced at the side is greater than that required to drive the reaction in reverse at the Thus, the device operates by continuously moving the hydrogen gas from high to low pressure and back again, while the excess electrical energy produced during this process can be used to do useful The device uses highly reversible electrochemical reactions and a temperature differential to pressurize gas, which can result in efficient conversion of thermal to electrical When used in reverse - it uses electrical energy for highly efficient air conditioning and refrigeration The device uses electrochemical reactions at different temperatures and pressures to create a potential difference, which can be harnessed to drive electrical It has the potential to generate electricity more efficiently than any device in use The JTEC operates in a closed, sealed environment it does not need fuel It is scalable it can be made small enough to harness body heat and power a wearable device, or large enough to capture waste heat from an industrial factory and convert it to usable It has distinct advantages over other devices: Solid State The JTEC has no moving parts, making it easier and less expensive to maintain than traditional Stirling Uses Electrochemical Reactions It uses electrochemical reactions to move and pressurize Other electrochemical converters, such as metal thermo electrochemical converters, employ similar concepts but use liquid sodium or potassium metal, which are highly Operates in a Wide Temperature Range It operates in greater temperature ranges than traditional electrochemical The January issue of Applied Energy Materials features a closer look at the JTEC technology: Fei Huang, Andrew Pingitore, Tedric Campbell, Andrew Knight, David Johnson, Lonnie Johnson, and Brian A Thermoelectrochemical Converter Using Polybenzimidazole (PBI) Membranes for Harvesting Heat ACS Applied Energy Materials 3 (1), DOI: acsaem.9b01830 A Thermoelectrochemical Converter Using Polybenzimidazole (PBI) Membranes for Harvesting Heat Energy To meet the rising energy demand and efficiently utilize a larger amount of waste heat energy from various devices and systems, here we report an innovative hermoelectrochemical converter which utilizes the electrochemical potential of a hydrogen pressure differential applied across a proton conductive The amount of energy available to the external load is the difference in electrical potential between that generated during a expansion stage and that required during a compression In this work, various phosphoric acid (PA)-doped polybenzimidazole (PBI) membranes, , , and m p-PBI, are prepared via the poly(phosphoric acid) (PPA) process and investigated to understand how the membrane chemistry affected device When operating a laboratory scale device at °C 200 °C and a pressure ratio of , exhibited the best performance (maximum current density of mA cm 2 , peak power density of mW cm 2 , and net efficiency of %) as compared with the other two PBIs due to its high proton Further increases in temperature or pressure differentials are expected to significantly improve the device All the reported results are consistent with the Nernst equation and thus further confirm the working principle of the thermoelectric conversion This transformational approach may allow for efficient generation of electricity from many diverse forms of waste READ THE FULL ARTICLE The JTEC offers highly efficient energy production in nearly any application where a heat or pressure differential is Farms The JTEC has the potential to be the most efficient device to convert solar thermal energy

Frequent Questions how do i get my ticket? You will receive a stream link and an access code on the confirmation page immediately after your payment is Take a screenshot when you see it for your records! You should also receive your ticket info via email, be sure to check your spam For some, but not all shows, you will also receive the ticket info via SMS What should I do if I didn’t get my ticket instantly on confirmation? If you did not receive your stream link and access code or didn’t make it to the confirmation screen, be sure to reach out to [email protected] and we’ll get you set up! How can I watch the show? You can go to the stream link either on your phone or your computer and then simply enter your access code to access the stream Can I watch the show on my TV? You can cast mirror a show directly to your TV from your phone or computer if you have an Apple TV or Roku With the proper adapters, it s possible to connect your device directly to your television (such as via HDMI). How many devices can I watch the show on? Your code will only work on one You will be able to get back to the stream page using that same device access code multiple times without HOW DO PASSES WORK? When you purchase a pass that includes multiple shows, you will receive a single stream link and access The link will give you access to all shows included with the pass and your access code will work on one device for each show! When will I receive the merch I bought? Most of the merchandise fulfillment is handled entirely by the artists, so it’s hard to give an exact delivery time Most merch is created on demand, so please allow 3 weeks after the date of the show for it to ship and additional delivery time unless otherwise Due to related delays in fulfillment, some merch may experience additional delays, but we are always working hard to get you your goods! What if my access code isn’t working? Contact [email protected] if your code isn t working for any What if I m having issues with my stream? Contact [email protected] if you’re having technical difficulties with the This includes any audio video issues you might be What’s the refund policy? There should be, but there isn’t. Why not? Turns out if you ask yourself that question enough times, you end up asking it out Then suddenly, you realize you’ve gathered a small team of skilled people who care about their local communities and also want to know the answer to that question, who then proceed to create this thing that should already exist but doesn’t. Before you know it, you’ve launched a pilot, seen it grow and thrive and be embraced by the community it lives to And by the time other cities start asking about why there’s no online store for their town, your “thing” has turned into a company that intends to help them answer the very same question that you started And that company is called (That’s us!) FAQ for Teens & Young Adults | Joon ï ï Our Therapists Resources Parents &Â Guardians Teens &Â Young Adults FAQ Parents &Â Guardians Teens &Â Young Adults About Get Started Our Therapists Resources Parents & Guardians Teens & Young Adults Parents & Guardians Teens & Young Adults About for teens & young adults If I m under , can I sign up for Joon myself? If you live in California, Oregon or Washington State and you are at least years old, you may request a free consultation without your parent having to sign During the consultation a Joon clinician will speak with you about situations where we will need to engage your parents, like if you want your parents to pay for therapy, or if we need their help to keep you Is parental consent required for therapy? Different states have different laws when it comes to seeking therapy as a In many states, if you re under the age of , you ll need a parent or guardian s This is because in order to provide any kind of treatment - medical or psychological - a patientâs consent must be If you are under the legal age to give consent as an adult in your state, then youâll need a parent or guardian s In Washington State, minors may receive mental health treatment if they are years or older without the consent of a parent or What should I do if I m nervous or uncomfortable asking my parents for help? Itâs totally normal to feel nervous talking about these topics, even with your Here are a few ideas for making the topic more approachable: When you talk to your parents, keep it simple, at least at You might start by telling your parents how you are feeling, what you would like help with, and that you think therapy might be the right tool to get you You can even use the following script if it makes it easier: âMom Dad, Iâve been feeling really (anxious, worried, sad, angry, ) for the last __ months, and itâs been making (school, homework, getting along with friends family, sports) super hard for Iâve tried a bunch of things to make it better, but I would like to see if going to a therapist could " If you have a good relationship with a teacher or your doctor, they can be a great resource for any questions you have that arenât answered here, or to practice asking for help! Remember that these are hard topics for everyone to talk about, but that doesn t make it wrong to bring them Even if it feels scary or uncomfortable, if you feel that you need help or support, talking to your parents is the right thing to You ve got this! What happens during a parent ? Will my conversations with my therapist be kept confidential? Can I ask my therapist not to share certain discussion topics with my parent? During a parent , your therapist will provide a general overview of the kinds of skills youâve been working on together but will not provide any specific details that youâve shared with him her. For example, if youâve been talking with your therapist about how to cope with parental pressure regarding schoolwork, your therapist might say generally that youâve been working on coping skills and motivation for You can absolutely ask your therapist not to share specific information with your parent and, assuming that information isnât about any immediate risk to your safety, your therapist will honor your privacy and not discuss those topics with your Are there community resources that may be able to help me without requiring me to talk to my parents guardians? Yes! In Washington State, TeenLink offers phone, text and chat Their teen volunteers are trained to listen to your concerns and talk with you about whateverâs on your mind â bullying, drug and alcohol concerns, relationships, stress, depression or any other issues youâre Calls and chats are Their phone number is (833.6546). I m worried about a friend, what should I do? Here are some helpful steps: If you are concerned that your friend is in danger, or might hurt themselves, tell a trusted Set aside a time to talk without Itâs best to talk over the phone or in person versus over Tell them what you see that is worrying Maybe they havenât been texting back lately, have been getting in fights, or have âjokedâ about hurting Tell them that you care about them and are wondering if everything is Listen to their reaction without Let them know you want to help if you If they want your help, you can give them information about or If they donât want help, thatâs okay! This is a free service to help independent workers obtain greater pay transparency, quicker access to work and the ability to connect with How long does it take to sign up? Signing up can take as little as two Just follow these steps: 1) Sign up here to create your free profile on SoloÂ 2) Securely link your work accounts (Uber, Doordash, Instacart, ) by logging in with your specific account How do I link my work accounts? You can link as many work accounts (Uber, Doordash, Instacart, ) as needed during the signup To do this, you use your login credentials (usually an email or phone number) and the password associated with that Some companies may ask you to verify the connection via a text or If you begin working with other platforms after you have signed up you can link those accounts by accessing the âLink Your Accountsâ page in the upper right hand corner of the Do you store my login information? Can you access my accounts ? Your login credentials are secure, encrypted and sent directly to your chosen app which allows us to securely retrieve trip We will never receive a copy of your login info and we are not able to access your When you disconnect a linked work account, we also delete all data related to that user and What will you do with my data? We use your data to help provide insights about your individual work history across multiple earnings This data is aggregated anonymously with others in the community to provide pay and performance We will delete your data if 1) you disconnect a linked work account or 2) if you delete your Solo Are you another rideshare delivery service? We donât compete with any of the rideshare, food, grocery or parcel delivery Using aggregated data, weâre here to help you better understand when, where and what job to work in your city so that you can earn more in less How do you actually help me make more in less time? Today, worker earnings on any one companyâs platform (Uber, Doordash, Instacart, ) can be extremely volatile day to day or even hour to They have different peak demand pay periods and different levels of supply Without transparent, market wide earnings information it can make your decision of where and when to work extremely Weâre here to give you all the information you need to see what jobs are paying the most in real time and make it easy to plan your schedule to hit your earnings goals Does Solo track my location and miles? Not at this We work with the information provided by your work accounts to help you estimate mileage, but plan to offer you the ability to track your miles with the Solo platform soon! Does this work in my city? Right now, Solo is only available in You can let us know you want access to Solo in your city by signing up for our waitlist or emailing us at Is Solo available in the app store?Â Not yet! Weâre only on the web at the moment, but will let you know when we offer a mobile app for iOS and How can I submit feedback? Information and data is sparse for workers - and when you can t count on what you ll be paid or finding the resources you need, it makes planning your professional life nearly The Solution A Platform that Puts Information in Your Hands We re setting out to rethink this space with a worker first We want to provide you with the information, resources and tools to achieve

My dear fellow Hero: This is 👋 I hope you and your family are doing Today I’m excited to give you an update on our Heroic social training platform and invite you to become one of our Founding More on that in a First, I’d like to quickly recap the last six months and then look forward to our official launch on April , (Less than days away!! 🚀) As you may recall, on December , , we sent this letter out to our Optimize community letting them know about our plans to create a new business called Heroic Public Benefit We shared our (ambitious) goal to make history as the first company to ever raise $5M via the new Reg CF equity crowdfunding regulations as part of our (even more ambitious) mission to change the course of history by creating a social training platform that would empower us all to be the best, most Heroic versions of Within hours we received support for OVER $5M from our Even now as I type that I get goosebumps and feeling the extraordinarily humbling and inspiring support we have been blessed to 🙇‍♂️ 🙏 (Note: After recommitting to my Heroic Sacred Vow, I reread a page of notes from our Founding Investors on why they were excited to invest (check out a sample here ) and I get tears in my eyes as I’m so moved by your belief in me and in our 🙇‍♂️ 🙏) Here’s a sample of the notes I read this morning: The simple answer is that the world desperately needs a change and Heroic is poised to be one of the defining catalysts of our age to realize Because the world is going crazy and I’d like to do something about This initiative is the one I’ve been waiting for, a community of heroes aimed at helping each other and the world I would love to join this journey! And, for curious souls, here’s my Sacred Vow… Long story a little shorter… A few months later, on March , , with the support of over 2,500 (!) Heroic Founding Investors from over (!) countries, we officially made history as the first company to ever close a $5M Reg CF equity crowdfunding as part of our $11M Seed round of After all that fun, it was time to get to work actually BUILDING our Heroic As you may know, we partnered with MetaLab, the company that built Slack, Uber Eats, and the app for Elon Musk’s new business, They’re We’re officially launching Heroic on April , With the support of Thrive Digital—the marketing firm behind companies like MasterClass, Snapchat, and Lululemon—we’re excited to see how quickly we can serve 1 million Now… We were going to wait until the Heroic platform was actually built before we started allowing people to sign up and then we thought… Why wait? 🤠 Let’s give people the chance to join our movement NOW and then share all the work over the next ten months so we can create some massive momentum and launch HEROICALLY And… Let’s generate some powerful cash flow NOW that we can immediately put right back into our product development so we can launch with an even more powerful platform on Day 1!!!
